caption: The chicken sandwich is so good.  Be careful when choosing your heat level, the hot is much closer to the crazy than the medium. The service was so good, when commenting that I might have made a mistake in my heat level they out of the blue offered to get me a new sandwich and the next level down.

I ordered hot,  but was inedible ,it was until i got in the store that I read all the hot peppers in the hot sandwich, well i couldn't eat, and i do eat spicy , on the garbage went. My husband had the mild,so was better.  The spiced fries potato salad (had pickles) were not that good really . The type of peppers used for the sayce should be on the menu. I have eaten in other places and whne they say hot, i imagine hot not something like this that swallowed my tongue and clogged my ears

Good flavor but the chicken was smaller than the bun not like the pics on he website that show a picture of a piece of chicken about three times the size of mine. Mine looked like 1 chicken tender on an expensive bun.

My absolute favorite fried chicken sandwich joint. I'm not kidding when I say I crave a sandwich every single week. I get the medium Nashville hot chicken and it's always phenomenal. The service has always been quick and I'm always satisfied after I go!
Best chicken sandwich in town and this is Chicago
Chill joint. Good food and beer.

Chicken and waffles at any time of the day?  Yes,  please.  Chicken and waffles( served with fried chicken, smoked bacon, spiced butter and hot maple syrup) is one of the signature dishes that you'll get at @frythecoop Add their maple syrup and you will have a delicious meal for your taste buds.  Try the Nashville Fried Chicken Sandwich ( fried chicken with coleslaw, pickles, Special Sauce on a brioche bun).  The combination is delicious!  We had pick up several times lately and food is warm and delicious.  Please remember masks are required.  Check out the cool decor and indoor dining with social distancing.  They've even added clear partitions at the bar.  Try Fry the Coop for some delicious Nashville style chicken!

Delicious Nashville fried chicken sandwich and fun ambience. Servers were super friendly and helpful. Word to the wise, this place knows how to apply the heat! I went with "Crazy" and could still feel the heartburn a few hours later. I'd recommend most people go with medium or hot. The only reason I knocked off a star is because the meal is a bit expensive ($11 for just the sandwich, $15 f you add fries/drink).

Fly the coop at Fry the Coop. Chicken sandwiches, staff, and  social distance friendly. Had a sandwich made with two glazed donuts. Good for a treat every once in a while.  Has a bar for those who enjoy this as their poison. Limited selection due to the situation, but "Pipeworks" beers do the job.

Chicken and waffles were amazing. So glad I switched it up this time around too! The smoked bacon, spiced butter, and maple syrup were just the warm up I needed today. Sorry no picture for this was a take out order. The waffles were not crisp when I got them back to the office only because it was a carry out order but the flavors were all there for sure!!! I would recommend this place to anyone looking to try Spicey chicken sandwhiches.
Awesome chicken sandwich, all of it was great. I'll definitely be a regular.

The crazy hot is CRAZY! it got to the point where my girlfriend went insane crying and running around the apartment!! 5/5 highly recommend for us spicy food lovers and 5/5 for quality service. Definitely will be back again without the crazy hot!
very tasty place. food takes long but its always fresh. The fries tast really good.
Some of the best chicken fingers I have ever had!
Quack quack love the Mac - Finger licking love the chicken - Potato salad very valid -
Just tried fry the coop for the first time and it was such a great experience Ajanee A made my experience awesome

They are awesome. They are quick and nice there. The chicken sandwich is one of the best I have had by far. I would give 5 stars but the price is outrageous because they don’t have meals. You have to pay for the drink separately and the fries!

This has got to be the best Nashville chicken sandwich i have had. Thats says alot because I have been to Nashville.  Now I was warned at the register, but because I eat plenty spicy food (I'm the type to go to Indian restaurants and ask for extra spicy), I thought "hot" would be nothing. Boy was I wrong. I'm still suffering the effects of last nights meal today. Next time I will do "medium" to enjoy the sandwich more. However, now that I know what I'm up against, I will be curious to try "insanity" as well in the future. I promise to be fully prepared 😆 🤣
Delicious chicken sandwiches! You can really taste the freshness with the first bite! I always go with the Spicy Butter Sandwich! My favorite level with it is 911!! Amazing ! Will be back for sure!
Love the insanity Nashville fried chicken

Have been meaning to try Fry the Coop since I moved to the area. We got it delivered and the sides (fries and mac and cheese) didn’t travel too well but I think they would definitely be good for dining in (hopefully one day). The hot chicken sandwiches were excellent and the best we have had outside of Nashville. No way I could ever have anything above a hot, I don’t know how people do it! The tender plate meal was excellent value for money too.

Got the Nashville hot chicken sandwich, "hot" heat level.  Can't really rate it at more than a 2 star because I was unable to eat more than one bite.   Waaay too hot.  The spice and heat intensify in your mouth to the point of coughing and hiccups.  Not enjoyable.  I like spicy food but this was nuts. I guess I'd try again and start with country style.

Came here with my girlfriend and overall had a bad experience. We waited for about 15 minutes only to find that our order had been plated and ready to go before we arrived. After getting home, we come to find that they mislabeled our sandwiches-- my girlfriend was given an extremely hot sandwich despite ordering a medium. I would not repeat this experience.
Love this chicken when It comes to the sandwiches. However the chicken tenders were over cooked and dry.

Out of all the times I’ve been there the employees are so rude. I do think this is the only thing they would have to work on otherwise the food is delicious.

The food is a 5/5 but unfortunately the lady working the pickup counter did not do a good job of checking for our order and forced us to wait 15 minutes saying the order wasn’t ready. We we asked again because it was so delayed they had it all along. Very disappointing service.
My girlfriend and I were surprised. It seemed really overpriced for what we got and my sandwich was dry (got the Tennessee). There was no sauce to put on mine either.

Very confused by all the people saying this place was just OK. This location has been nothing but delicious every time I’ve gone. The  chicken is delicious and very flavorful, the coleslaw and the bun is also amazing. I have no desire to know how many calories is in that sandwich but it’s definitely worth a treat yourself moment!
Great chicken sandwich

Wow!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! I went here on the fly, my friend recommended it to me and I was SO impressed. Since I’ve tried the mild chicken sandwich and fries nothing else has came close. 🔥 Highly recommend!

this place is a gem! everything on the menu is made fresh & delicious, from the tenders to the sandwiches to the seasoned fries (all w / a touch of sweetness!) plus staff are friendly and willing to help explain things on the menu (like the heat levels). huge props and thanks to the whole Fry the Coop team.

Great place!  We stopped here when our AirBnb canceled on us last minute and needed to figure out a new plan.  Bartender was nice, drinks were good, didn't eat the food though.  Fun joint!

Might be the best chicken sandwich I've had!... I ordered with the "hot" heat level and it was almost too much heat to eat but it was worth it.  House fries were good but not great.  My only real complaint might be the price ... A bit overpriced IMO .... $30 for two people and we shared a drink and fries. Very good Chicken

It was really good and my date and I got free heart shaped doughnuts for valentine's! Great flavors!

Amazing food and service! The owner is super friendly. My go-to is the original sandwich with mild heat. Perfect ratio of crispy chicken to toppings. Yummmmm!  Great Chicago drink menu. If you’re out of town, you should try the Chicago Handshake ;)

The tenders were great.  I had the medium, which had a nice little kick to it.  I'll probably try the hot next time.  I liked the potato salad better than the coleslaw.  The bartender was great, but they serve the beer in plastic cups.  They should get some proper glassware.

Let me start this review off with a disclaimer:  I've been to probably every hot chicken place in Chicago and many of the greats in the southern US.  I'm comparing Fry The Coop to some of the greatest hot chicken places there are.  Long story short: it's a really good place for a chicken sandwich better than Popeye's and a couple beers but I can't say it's on the same level as other hot chicken places in Chicago.  Pros: Great atmosphere, friendly wait staff, sides were very tasty (tried mac & cheese and fries), and the sandwich I got was overall great - disclaimer on the chicken itself in a moment.  The bar looked like it had a great selection of beer on tap but we didn't get anything to drink.  Cons:  On the dinner menu there were only chicken sandwiches, tenders, and chicken & waffles as entrees on the menu.  No bone-in chicken.  I'm a huge fan of hot chicken and was hoping to order two pieces of chicken alone so I was kind of disappointed that wasn't an option.  Oh well, reviews for the sandwiches are amazing so I went for the Nashville Fried Chicken Sandwich.  Next I had to choose a spice level.  I typically like very spicy foods.  Not off the charts spicy, but prefer something with a good kick.  My fiancé opted for the "Medium" heat level (2/5), which she usually does, and i prefer to go for something hotter so I went with "Hot".  Keep in mind, at the time of this review, "Hot" is number 3 on the list of their 5 total spice levels.  There were two levels above this - Crazy and Insane.  I went to the online menu to check if this was correct and it is different online, which is interesting.  Anyways, I ask for Hot and the cashier gives me a warning that it has habaneros in it.  That's fine, I like habaneros and I'm familiar with the heat level that comes with them and I told him so.  So our food comes and it looks really good.  The brioche bun was fresh and tasty.  I really like the sauce they put on the sandwich as well.  The problem was that this thing was WAY too hot.  My fiancé was enjoying her medium spice level with no problem at all while I was sweating my way through this sandwich.  If you've been to Prince's in Nashville, the Hot level I got was probably between their x-hot and xx-hot levels.  I don't think there's a spice level here that's right for me.  That paired with the fact that they don't have just regular bone-in chicken is a deal breaker.  I think there are other, much better Nashville hot chicken places in the city.
Amazing Nashville hot chicken sandwich, beer list is chicago inspired with great choices..
Absolutely delicious fried chicken sandwiches. Their seasoned fries are also great. The medium spice level had a nice kick to it; will definitely be ordering the hot next time!

So lucky to have this place right next door to where I live. The atmosphere is great and the chicken is HOT! I went with the Crazy spice and the lady behind the counter asked me if I was ready for Carolina Reaper hot and I confirmed I was. Definitely the hottest chicken I ever had but it was good. Can’t wait to go back
I’ve been to the one in the southwest suburbs, and this one is just as good. Great chicken sandwiches and tenders! The spice is no joke though.
Best Nashville Hot Chicken sandwich in town. Hands down.
Place is awesome to get a spicy chicken sandwich and a beer. Friendly and fast service.

Gotta say this exceeded expectations! Love a crispy hot chicken sandwich, been to Hattie B’s in Nashville & came in this evening for a quick dinner. Everyone was so friendly & the food came out quickly. it was Delicious! I don’t have any pictures because I basically inhaled my sandwich. I had the Chicken & Cheese sandwich at the Mild Level + Mac&cheese. My hubby got the spicy butter fried chicken at the Hot level. The bun is a Brioche Bun, the Chicken was super crispy, pickles we’re perfect. My mild spice was perfect, I had a hint of heat that grew over time - I could have probably tried the medium. My husband loved the Hot heat level (it was too much for me). Mac & cheese was a small portion but enough for us to share. We will definitely be back! Gotta try all The sandwiches, sides & the chicken & waffles which smelled insane!

My girlfriend and I live in the neighborhood and were walking by yesterday when we noticed the beautifully painted brick building and signage out front.  Excited to see something new on the Chicago Ave strip, we decided to stop in and give the place a try - so GLAD we did!  The Nashville style fried chicken was amazing, they know what they're doing.  I ordered the HOT dry rub on my chicken and boy they are not messing around with spice.... it had ghost pepper in it and it sure was HOT (but that's how I like it).  The portioning is also good - between my entree and sides I had leftovers which is always a plus.  What stood out to us the most was the service and care we received.  After we ordered by the register, they later brought our drinks and food to our table (normal).  Although, during our meal we were checked-in on by staff members multiple times.  They made sure we had enough dipping sauce and that everything was kosher with our food.  Unfortunately, what my girlfriend ordered turned out to be too spicy and she was struggling with the heat.  Without any action on our end, the attentive staff noticed and approached our table to make sure she was satisfied.  They were genuine and addressed the spicy issue quickly by remaking her food.  After that she was able to enjoy her chicken sandwich and we both were very happy with our entire experience.  Everything was delicious!  In all, I'm glad they are so close and look forward to visiting again as well as taking me guest to here.

We went opening night and got the Nashville Fried Chicken Sandwich with medium heat.  It was great.  This is the perfect amount of heat for good flavor.  We also had the seasoned fries which were good.  You can order there or to go.
